text: Michael Gordon Bracewell (born 14 February 1991 in Masterton) is a New Zealand cricketer who has played for Otago and Wellington in the Plunket Shield and scored 141 not out in the Super Smash to record the highest Twenty20 score in New Zealand cricket in 2021/22. He is the nephew of John Bracewell and Brendon Bracewell. He is the cousin of Doug Bracewell and comedian Melanie Bracewell. ==Other websites== * Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:New Zealand cricketers Category:Sportspeople from North Island
